      <subsection xml:id="subsec-Forming Simple Linear Inequalities in real Life Situations.">
      <title>Forming Simple Linear Inequalities in real Life Situations.</title>
      <activity>
        <p>
          Bag <em>A</em> conatins <em>x</em> mangoes.
          Two mangoes are added to it. The total number of mangoes is 
          either equal to or less than the number of mangoes in bag B,
          which contains 30 mangoes.
        </p>
        <p><term>In Pairs</term></p>
        <ol>
          <li><p>Add 2 mangoes to <em>x</em></p></li>
          <li><p>Compare the quantities <em>x+2</em> and <em>30.</em></p></li>
          <li><p>Discuss and share your results.</p></li>
        </ol>
      </activity>

      <example>
        <p>
          Jane had some oragnges, She gave Mwara <em>5</em> of them.
          She was left with at most <em>12</em> of them.
          Write an inequality to represent this statement.
        </p>
        <term>Solution.</term>
        <p>Let the number of oranges be <em>x</em></p>
        <p><em>x-5</em> is less than or equal to <em>12</em></p>
        <p><em>x-5&gt;12.</em></p>
      </example>

